[49m[38;5;9m- 132     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Local Validation Required** | Vendor or external models must be validated on local population before clinical deployment. Subgroup-stratified validation is part of this. The validation should use a hold-out time period (not patient split) to capture temporal drift. Validation should compare against the existing standard of care (typically the in-use track-and-trigger system). |
